HEADWORD: Permiss
<hw>Per*miss"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Permit</er>.]</ety> <def>A permitted choice; a rhetorical figure in
which a thing is committed to the decision of one's opponent.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Permissibility</ent>⟦br⟧
